Set Up Omni-Channel

Omni-Channel integrates seamlessly into both console and standard apps. To set up Omni-Channel: Customize Application.

Omni-Channel is available in Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

We recommend using Enhanced Omni-Channel. Enhanced Omni-Channel features better experiences for agents and supervisors than Standard Omni-Channel, and future Omni-Channel features are developed on Enhanced Omni-Channel.

Create a queue and routing configuration, select your support agents, and add the Omni-Channel component to your default Lightning Service Console app with a quick guided setup flow.

Enable Omni-Channel to let agents manage their work in different service channels from the same app. Then turn on Omni-Channel features based on your business needs.

Add the Omni-Channel Component to an App To give agents easy access to Omni-Channel, add it where they workâ€”in a Lightning app.

Use Omni Supervisor to monitor agent workloads and the status of work items that are routed by Omni-Channel. Agents can raise flags on work items when they require assistance from a supervisor.

Set up agents to complete work requests in Omni-Channel. After agents are set up, they can manage their work from the Omni-Channel component in a Lightning app.

Prioritize, distribute, and assign records to teams who share workloads with queues. Queue members can jump in to take ownership of any record in a queue.

Use out-of-the-box report types to join agent work with the objects most commonly used with Omni-Channel. Make custom reports on such data as workload by case type, active time by channel type, and so on.

Set up Omni-Channel to route incoming work items from different service channels to qualified, available agents in your contact center at the new Omni-Channel setup home.

Enable and Configure Omni-Channel Enable Omni-Channel features based on your business needs.
title: Setting Up Salesforce Service Cloud Omni-Channel
